cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the properties of convolutional neural networks (ConvNets) and their ability to memorize training data, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the experiments are conducted on image datasets. The paper also touches upon the issue of overfitting, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to infer membership, which involves the use of lower layers of the network, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
